icular we show SNe feedback to be more important than\nradiative feedback, the presence of which we find does not influence either the\ntotal stellar mass or overall ionising photon budget. Thus, if SNe feedback is\neffective at suppressing star formation in high redshift galaxies, we find that\nphotoionization feedback does not lead to self-regulation of the reionization\nprocess as has been thought.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Mar 2012 01:18:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 15 Oct 2012 23:27:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
